node.text: Do you have more weekend projects than you have weekend? Here’s how home improvement expert Joe Truini gets his outdoor space looking great for the warm weather ahead.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by The Weather Channel in Colorado River. May be an image of road and text that says 'Colorado River Drought to Lead to Unprecedented Measure'.

node.text:
For the first time ever, the federal government has declared a water shortage on the Colorado River.

The river that supplies water to some 40 million people across the West has seen water levels decline in some reservoirs as much as 50% in just five years.

As a result, mandatory water cuts will begin on Jan. 1 in Arizona and Nevada, and those restrictions could be expanded further if the drought worsens and water levels continue to drop.

It's yet another symptom of a warming world, climate scientists say.

Tap the link in our bio for the full story.

📸: Patrick T. Fallon/AFP via Getty Images

#ColoradoRiver #drought #ClimateChange #GlobalWarming

node.text:
This Sunday, Aug. 15, 2021, photo provided by U.S. Forest Service-Superior National Forest shows a rapidly growing wildfire in northeastern Minnesota that has prompted some evacuations, the U.S. Forest Service said Monday, Aug. 16, 2021. The fire was spotted around 3 p.m. Sunday near Greenwood Lake, about 15 miles southwest of Isabella, in the Superior National Forest.

By Tuesday, the fire had burned more than 3 square miles. Authorities said about 75 homes have been evacuated.

📸: Nick Petrack/Forest Service-Superior National Forest via AP

#GreenwoodFire #Minnesota #wildfire

node.text:
Firefighters are working hard to beat back the flames of the Dixie Fire which came within a few miles of Susanville, California, Lassen County’s seat, Monday into early Tuesday. The fire moved aggressively overnight due to heavy winds, and a red flag warning was issued for Tuesday until near midnight.

The blaze burned structures after jumping Highway 395 south of Janesville, California, on Monday night and evacuations were issued in the town. 
The Dixie Fire has burned more than 944 square miles and was still only 31% contained on Tuesday.

Click the link in our bio to see more powerful images of the largest fire burning in the U.S.

Photo by AP/Ethan Swope 

#DixieFire #wildfire #WesternWildfiresF

node.text:
The situation in Haiti went from bad to worse as Tropical Depression Grace, now a tropical storm, dumped torrential rain on the earthquake-stricken areas.

This left many survivors, who are now living outside either because the quake left them homeless or because they fear additional damage from aftershocks, exposed to the elements as the tropical system moved over the island Monday.

More than 1,400 people died and 6,000 others were injured in the earthquake. It isn't yet known if Grace triggered mudslides as it dumped rain on the already unstable land, or if there were additional deaths because of the storm.

Tap the link in our bio for the slideshow of the Haiti quake aftermath, and to see the complete forecast for Tropical Storm Grace.

📸: AP Photo/Joseph Odelyn

#Grace #Haiti #earthquake #weather

node.text:
The Dixie Fire, the largest wildfire currently burning in the U.S., is threatening nearly 15,000 structures. The blaze has already destroyed more than 1,000 homes and businesses since it began in mid-July.  The Dixie Fire has burned more than 890 square miles so far and was 31% contained on Monday. 

Weekend thunderstorms fueled the fire’s advance into Taylorsville, California, where several structures burned. The accompanying rain did little to help. 

Click the link in our bio to read more.

Photo by AP/Eugene Garcia

#Wildfire #DixieFire #CaliforniaWildfire

node.text:
One major reason hurricanes and tropical storms are dangerous weather phenomena is because they can cause catastrophic flash flooding.

Floods have led to $260 billion in damage in the U.S. over the past 30 years, and over 100 deaths annually, on average, since 2015.

Since Tropical Storm Fred is forecast to drop a lot of rain on the Southeast over the next few days, tap the link in our bio for a few tips to help keep you and your loved ones safer (and drier) in a flood.

📸 : Fajrin Raharjo Raharjo/EyeEm/Getty Images

#floods #Fred #weather #TropicalStorm #safety

node.text:
Tropical Storm Fred is expected to make landfall Monday along the Florida Panhandle.

It will bring flooding rain, gusty winds, storm surge and isolated tornadoes.

Soaking rainfall and possible flooding from Fred and its remnant will also spread inland across parts of Alabama, Georgia, the western Carolinas and mid-Atlantic region.

We are constantly tracking all the latest developments on The Weather Channel and The Weather Channel app, so tune in and log on for all the latest.

Tap the link in our bio for the complete forecast and tag your friends who are in the path of this storm.

📸: @noaa
